The order of 10 parameters of the USER's function FORCE
(INTERIOR in the material, (pesantor,hydro static pressure,...)
 or EXTERIOR on the boundary)
at time TEMPS, at point X,Y,Z, 
for the PLSVO of type number NO_TYPE_OBJECT
(1:POINT, 2:LINE, 3:SURFACE, 4:VOLUME, 5:OBJECT )
the directory number NO_OBJECT
the number NO_COMP of the FORCE
the 3 components XN,YN,ZN of the BOUNDARY NORMAL VECTOR of NORM=1
to facilitate the user input of normal forces on 3D surface or 
2D line boundaries, directed to the exterior,
must be

FORCE( TEMPS, X,Y,Z, NO_TYPE_OBJET, NO_OBJET, NO_COMP, XN,YN,ZN ) 

and be programmed with respect to LU grammar
(cf documentation and examples of the debut menu)

All these parameters will be initialized during its call.
These parameters can be used or not, but have to be present
in the definition of the FORCES.

ATTENTION:
The NORMAL VECTOR is ONLY DEFINED for the SURFACES of a 3D OBJECT,
or the LINES of a 2D OBJECT.

In any other case, POINTS in 2D or 3D, LINES of a 3D OBJECT,
SURFACES of a 2D OBJECT, LINES of an 3D OBJECT, the SURFACES
of a 2D-OBJECT, VOLUMES of a 3D OBJECT, the 3 components
XN, YN, ZN will be initialized to ZERO.
 
EXAMPLE: 
deffunc force( t, x,y,z, no_type_objet, material, no_comp, xn,yn,zn );
if  material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'steel' )
then 
  if no_comp=1
  then  force=1e6; 
  else  force=5e4; 
  endif ;
else
  if  material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'copper' )
  then 
    if no_comp=1
    then force= 2e3 ;
    else force=-1e4 ;
    endif;  
  endif;   
endif;
endfunc;

Remark: the LU function nuobjt( p1, p2 ) gives the
number of the PLSVO of type p1 with the name p2.
